The paper proposes a method for conditional density estimation (CDE) and dimensionality reduction (DR) in high-dimensional space. This is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of supervised learning. The paper also mentions experiments on various datasets including humanoid robot transition and computer art, indicating a focus on robotics and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions experiments on humanoid robot transition, indicating a focus on robotics, which suggests cs.RO (Robotics) as a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to CDE and DR, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.SD (Systems and Control).
